<paragraph blockId="14.[125,245,961,985]" box="[125,245,961,985]" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis box="[125,245,961,985]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[125,1172,1009,1683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">
<typeStatus box="[125,233,1009,1033]" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">Holotype</typeStatus>
an anterior fragment, slightly damaged, 
<quantity box="[727,807,1009,1033]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="14" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[888,953,1009,1033]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide, 69 setigers; longest median fragment 
<quantity box="[428,508,1042,1066]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[586,651,1042,1066]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide, 69 setigers; shortest fragment 
<quantity box="[1092,1172,1042,1066]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[191,279,1074,1098]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
wide, 38 setigers. Integument rugose, verrucae sparse, minute, concentrated on anterior end and dorsal cirri.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[125,1172,1009,1683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">
Prostomium fused with peristomium; palps biarticulate, palpostyles tiny rounded, directed ventrally. Antennae globose, smooth, rising from low protuberances on the base of palps, reaching the anterior margin of palps. Tentacular cirri cirriform, dorsal ones 1.2 times longer and 1.5 times wider than the ventral, those on the right side incomplete, the ventral is missing (
<figureCitation box="[344,466,1269,1293]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="16.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[129,1169,263,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-47@16.[125,1173,255,1548]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 4. (A–D) Pilargis angeli n. sp. UANL-1474: (A) anterior end in dorsal view (verrucae are mostly restricted to parapodia); (B) right setiger 10 in anterior view; (C) median setiger in anterior view; (D) right setiger 60 in anterior view. (E) Pilargis sp. juvenile BLM 85401 BF1, complete organism in dorsal view, slightly distorted by cover slip. Scale bars: 225 mm (A); 120 mm (B–D); 500 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4669316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4669316/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">Figure 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[125,1172,1009,1683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">
First setiger with dorsal cirri longer than tentacular cirri, longer than following cirri. Anterior 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Joannis" authorityYear="1912" box="[233,348,1335,1359]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Parapodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">parapodia</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[366,483,1335,1359]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="16.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[129,1169,263,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-47@16.[125,1173,255,1548]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 4. (A–D) Pilargis angeli n. sp. UANL-1474: (A) anterior end in dorsal view (verrucae are mostly restricted to parapodia); (B) right setiger 10 in anterior view; (C) median setiger in anterior view; (D) right setiger 60 in anterior view. (E) Pilargis sp. juvenile BLM 85401 BF1, complete organism in dorsal view, slightly distorted by cover slip. Scale bars: 225 mm (A); 120 mm (B–D); 500 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4669316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4669316/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">Figure 4B</figureCitation>
) with some verrucae over the back and cirrostyles; dorsal cirrophore thick, globose; no traces of large glandular areas in the middle of the cirrophore nor epidermal glands, but a diffuse spotted pattern of glands in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Joannis" authorityYear="1912" box="[922,1037,1400,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Parapodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">parapodia</taxonomicName>
of median fragments. Ventral cirri elongate, about one-third as long as dorsal cirri; dorsal cirrostyles cirriform, very long, some with a distal swelling, 1.2–1.5 times cirrophore length. Median and posterior 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Joannis" authorityYear="1912" box="[298,413,1497,1521]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Parapodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">parapodia</taxonomicName>
similar (
<figureCitation box="[525,622,1497,1521]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="16.[125,185,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[129,1169,263,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-47@16.[125,1173,255,1548]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 4. (A–D) Pilargis angeli n. sp. UANL-1474: (A) anterior end in dorsal view (verrucae are mostly restricted to parapodia); (B) right setiger 10 in anterior view; (C) median setiger in anterior view; (D) right setiger 60 in anterior view. (E) Pilargis sp. juvenile BLM 85401 BF1, complete organism in dorsal view, slightly distorted by cover slip. Scale bars: 225 mm (A); 120 mm (B–D); 500 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4669316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4669316/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">Figure 4</figureCitation>
C–D), without verrucae; ventral cirri shorter, cirriform, longer than setal lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[125,1172,1009,1683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="132">Most neurosetae limbate, limbus denticulate, distally unidentate, straight, tend to curl distally; longer in the superior than in the inferior portion of setal bundle. Some superior setae smooth capillaries. Pygidium unknown. Brain posterior lobes reach setiger 1. Pharynx not everted; gut diverticula start in setiger 2.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[138,250,136,160]" box="[138,250,136,160]" pageId="15" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis box="[138,250,136,160]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="133">Discussion</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[138,1185,184,304]" pageId="15" pageNumber="133">
<taxonomicName authority="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Harris, 2006" authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Harris" authorityYear="2006" box="[138,292,184,208]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="133" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="angeli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[138,292,184,208]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="133">Pilargis angeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[301,366,184,208]" pageId="15" pageNumber="133" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Webster)" authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1879" baseAuthorityName="Webster" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[577,853,184,208]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Phronia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tardigrada">
<emphasis box="[577,724,184,208]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="133">P. tardigrada</emphasis>
(Webster)
</taxonomicName>
; they differ because the first have verrucae on its anterior end, while the second has verrucae restricted to parapodial lobes. Further, the size of cirrostyles is different, being very long in 
<taxonomicName authority="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Harris, 2006" authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Harris" authorityYear="2006" box="[949,1047,248,272]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="133" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="angeli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[949,1047,248,272]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="133">P. angeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1057,1126,248,272]" pageId="15" pageNumber="133" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and conical and shorter in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1879" baseAuthorityName="Webster" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[402,549,280,304]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Phronia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tardigrada">
<emphasis box="[402,549,280,304]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="133">P. tardigrada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
